The United States and France are working together to combat climate change, promote clean energy, and protect the environment. Both countries are committed to reducing greenhouse gas emissions and increasing renewable energy usage. They are urging all nations to join in an ambitious global agreement on climate change. The United States and France also collaborate on clean energy and climate solutions through various forums and organizations. They are partners in the development of nuclear energy and strive to improve nuclear safety. Additionally, the two countries work together in Africa to combat wildlife trafficking and promote conservation. They also collaborate on maritime affairs, particularly in the creation and management of marine protected areas.